        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 7:13PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 712 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Grant, or 12 miles northeast of Guntersville, moving southeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Scottsboro, Guntersville, Rainsville, Henagar, Sylvania, Fyffe,
Powell, Grant, Geraldine, and Section.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
